This paper deals with the evaluation of a call-by-need lambda calculus, which is a programming language concept. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of this concept using an abstract machine, which falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also involves the use of a control stack, which is a data structure commonly used in computer science, making it relevant to the Data Structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a theoretical approach to the problem, which could place it in the Theory of Computation (cs.THEORY) sub-category.
